Dr Poehling says the most important things people can do to protect themselves now is get the primary #covid19 vaccination series, if they haven't, and get their annual flu shot. Next up, kids under 12 and booster considerations for people who got Moderna & J&J. (5)

I just spoke with Dr Katherine Poehling from Wake Forest, one of the CDC advisory cmte members whose vote was ostensibly overruled by @CDCDirector Dr Rochelle Walensky on Pfizer #covid19 booster.

I say ostensibly, because Dr Poehling says she feels like Dr Walensky listened. (1)

TODAY! 1:30pmET: a big dose of biotech talk on @CNBCTheExchange with @KellyCNBC 

I'll be on w @matthewherper & Alethia Young and we'll dig into a few big topics in medicines/vaccines for #covid19 & Alzheimer's

I am excited

Biden says he's going to get his #covid19 booster shot as soon as he can get it done

Tells Moderna & J&J folks they still have a high degree of protection, scientists working day/night to determine whether and when they need a booster shot

Biden says 60M Americans are now eligible for a booster once they're 6 months out from second Pfizer #covid19 shot

20M who received Pfizer shot at least 6 months ago are eligible today

(Note: millions who received Moderna or J&J 6+ months ago... not eligible)

At CDC ACIP meeting, one panelist asks whether recommendation on Pfizer #covid19 booster could wait for a month, if Moderna booster might be through FDA by then, so booster recs could be made for both simultaneously.

2-day CDC Advisory Committee on Immunization Practices meeting kicking off now. Today they'll discuss considerations around boosters as well as updated information about #covid19 vaccines in pregnancy; tomorrow will include a vote on Pfizer booster.

Earlier on @SquawkCNBC, @andrewrsorkin asked Pfizer CEO about comparisons between Moderna & Pfizer #covid19 vaccines and suggestions Moderna protection is more durable. Bourla doesn't agree: https://t.co/6NWc2B5uhi

Gilead out w new results on remdesivir for just diagnosed #covid19 patients not in hospital, but at high risk of progression:

Says 3 days of IV treatment reduced risk of hospitalization by 87% by day 28 vs placebo

Appears similar to monoclonal antibodies, but 3 days of IV?
Pfizer CEO @AlbertBourla joins us next on @SquawkCNBC to discuss new agreement w US govt to supply 500M #covid19 vaccine doses for donation globally, plus boosters, vaccines for kids - tune in

-J&J also updates on phase 3 1-shot #covid19 vaccine results, noting "somewhat lower vaccine efficacy against severe/critical disease caused by variants" - 93% against reference strain, 72% overall. J&J says analysis included countries with high lambda & gamma in circulation (3/)

-J&J cites real-world study of 1-shot #covid19 vaccine that suggests "no evidence of reduced effectiveness over the study duration, including when the Delta variant became dominant in the U.S." (conducted March-late July 2021): 81% VE for hospitalization; 79% for infections (2/)

J&J'ers, your day for data has arrived. Co out with a ton of new information (press released) on its #covid19 vaccine:

-2 shots given 2 months apart = 94% efficacy against moderate-severe/critical Covid in US; 75% globally

-booster to 1 dose at 6 months = 9-12x antibodies (1/)

Resurfacing this, on Moderna #covid19 vaccine timeline for kids 6-11, given Pfizer news. Moderna also looking at a half dose for kids in this age range (Pfizer goes down to age 5): https://t.co/yI8AvIVZl0

Availability depends on when cos submit the filing & length of FDA review https://t.co/8VM0fsB8NO

On new vote, for EUA for Pfizer booster for people 65+ and those at high risk of severe Covid:

Yes: 18
No: 0
Abstain: 0

NEW voting Q for FDA advisory panel:

Based on totality of scientific evidence available... do known and potential benefits outweigh known and potential risks of Pfizer/BioNTech #covid19 vaccine booster at least 6 months out for use in:
-65+
-those at high risk of severe Covid

FDA VRBPAC members now discussing which ages or other groups they‚Äôd support #covid19 booster for - some say 50, some 60, others include people with comorbidities, and healthcare workers.

Likelihood of FDA approving a booster broadly and leaving clinical recs to CDC ACIP?

FDA's Dr Peter Marks: "It's no secret here that there is still debate over the need for an additional #covid19 vaccine at this stage of the pandemic, but the emerging evidence from our Israeli colleagues is very helpful."

FDA's Dr Doran Fink notes 300 is on lower end of experience with boosters for other diseases, which range from about 300 to 1,000 with varying levels of post-marketing surveillance, but notes large database of clinical trials supporting first 2 doses for #covid19
